- `MEV`: the proposal still does not fully solve perspective. You need three linked legs: proposer revenue, searcher revenue, user/protocol loss. Without the mirror loss leg, extractive yield looks cleaner than it is.
- `Nexus` and `DOVs`: they should not share a single conceptual row. Both warehouse risk, but one is short correlated default/claims severity and the other is short vol/skew/gamma. Very different stress behavior.
